A presidential aspirant on the platform of the National Rescue Movement (NRM), Prof. Benedicta Egbo on Sunday charged Nigerians to desist from recycling the current crop of politicians that have failed the country. Speaking in Asaba while declaring her intention to serve Nigerians, declared that past and current political leaders owe Nigerians for the situation of the country, saying that Nigeria has never had it so bad. The country has retrogressed rather than progressed. She maintained that corruption has increased significantly under the administration of the current government at the Federal level, saying that the corruption in Nigeria is so that it should be considered a National disease. -Advertisement- She said that the frequent cross-carpeting of politicians from APC to PDP is evidence of unprincipled leaders who only care about their selfish interests and lack